  "term": "def:function-bounded-below",
  "kind": "Definition",
  "title": "Bounded Below Function",
  "root": "",
  "statement": "Let $A\\subseteq\\mathbb{R}$ and let $f:A\\to\\mathbb{R}$. The function\n$f$ is bounded below on $A$ if there exists $m\\in\\mathbb{R}$ such that\n\\[\n m\\leq f(x)\n \\qquad (x\\in A).\n\\]",
